A_362 - It happens that when we have information and we convey it via the internet to other people, we happen to think that &ldquo;it has reached its destination&rdquo;. In reality this does not necessarily happen: the delivery of information to the correct recipients also requires commitment to ensure that what we want to share produces the maximum result. It happens that when we understand something valuable, we can only make one or two uses of it before it is lost. In certain cases it is also necessary to &ldquo;mop up&rdquo; valuable information from conversations that had been conveyed in personal communications to people close to us, in order to be able to reuse something that had already been written.